### Description

Hi,

I submit a json request as couple login + password for connecting to an external server. The server receives the json couple and if the couple is right, sent a json for indicating that the state is connected, otherwise unconnected.

On the server side, all is OK (it is a Perl Dancer2):

```
% curl --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
  --request POST \
  --data '{"login":"PK","password":"PK"}' \
  http://localhost:5000/connect
{"ConnectionState":"connected"}

% curl --header "Content-Type: application/json" --request POST --data
'{"login":"PK","password":""}' http://localhost:5000/connect
{"ConnectionState":"unconnected"}

% curl --header "Content-Type: application/json" --request POST
http://localhost:5000/connect
{"ConnectionState":"unconnected"}

% curl  http://localhost:5000/connect
{"status":404,"title":"Error 404 - Not Found","message":"/connect"}

% curl --header "Content-Type: application/json" --request POST
http://localhost:5000/connect
{"ConnectionState":"unconnected"}
```
Firefox tells me that the json response is uncorrect:

```
 Uncaught (in promise) SyntaxError: JSON.parse: unexpected
end of data at line 1 column 1 of the JSON data
```

But its network debugger shows a correct negotiation and a nice json response.

Chromium (I work on Linux) stops immediately with the error on json response:

```
p.js:34 Uncaught (in promise) SyntaxError: Unexpected end of input (at App.js:34:1)
    at App.js:34:1
```
and its network debugger indicates no negotiation.

The server logs are in phase with the two both behaviors.

Since the server seems OK without my native React script, I suspect now a bug anywhere in the process inside Native React (may be in my script, but it is enough classical and you can find it anywhere on the net as example).

I have isolated the bug in a single script that I put into the bug report.

I have changed of nvm version without change.

